40 protective factors, warning signs, response procedures, and
41 postvention support.
42 5. For purposes of this section, the [term] following
43 terms mean:
44 (1) "Licensed educator", [shall refer to] any teacher
45 with a certificate of license to teach issued by the state
46 board of education or any other educator or administrator
47 required to maintain a professional license issued by the
48 state board of education;
49 (2) "Postvention", an organized response in the
50 aftermath of a suicide to facilitate the healing of
51 individuals from the grief and distress of suicide loss, to
52 mitigate other negative effects of exposure to suicide, or
53 to prevent suicide among people who are at high risk after
54 exposure to suicide.
